---
import { LuExternalLink } from "react-icons/lu"
---

<section class="flex flex-col gap-y-6 print:gap-y-1" id="about">
  <div class="space-y-2">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold" id="about">About Me</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
    <div class="text-muted-foreground">
      I'm a Software Developer from Bangladesh. I was introduced to programming
      with C during my undergraduate studies, but it never really clicked. It
      wasn't until my second year, when I started building simple web pages with
      JavaScript, that programming began to make sense. Seeing code produce
      immediate results in the browser changed how I approached programming.
    </div>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground">
      After graduating, I joined Zventures LLC as a Frontend Engineering Intern
      and was promoted to Frontend Developer six months later. Working on
      production SaaS applications showed me that software development is about
      more than shipping features. It also means building maintainable systems,
      taking ownership, improving performance, writing reusable code, and
      leaving a codebase better postion for the next engineer to work with than
      I initially found.
    </div>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground">
      Outside of work, I spend time reading documentation, building personal
      projects, and learning technologies beyond my day-to-day responsibilities.
      Recently, I've been focused on backend development and AI-assisted
      workflows. I use AI to explore ideas, automate repetitive tasks, and
      understand unfamiliar technologies, but I still believe good software
      comes from thoughtful engineering decisions not blindly accepting
      generated code.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
